    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-12-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="584"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d584">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.73/465</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Third Assistant Secretary of State</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">Merle-Smith</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-12-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1920</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Vallance</hi>: I telephoned the British Embassy
                    Saturday and talked to Mr. Tennant.<note n="1" xml:id="d584fn1">Mr. H. V.
                        Tennant, Secretary, temporarily attached to the British Embassy.</note> I
                    informed him of the situation, telling him that we must at least have some
                    security that the cable would not be laid within the territorial waters of the
                    United States to avoid embarrassing complications; that the best thing to do
                    would be to have the cable taken off the vessel in England. Hp said he agreed
                    with me that this should be done and would telegraph London <pb facs="0788"
                        n="698" xml:id="pg_698"/> in regard to the matter, and that if they could
                    not have that done they would try and arrange for some assurance which would
                    satisfy us.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Van</hi> S. M[<hi rend="smallcaps">erle</hi>]-S[<hi
                            rend="smallcaps">mith</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
